div.div:
Add support for Redis aggregate connections and search queries
This update introduces key classes of Redis including 'ACL', 'PredisException' and 'Aggregate', providing enhanced command handling in geospatial search queries and time series. It also broadens the .gitignore file to include vendor and composer.lock files, supporting better version control.

Add new files to geocoder package and update .gitignore
This commit includes addition of several new files to the 'willdurand/geocoder' package. This includes PHP classes like AbstractProvider, Address, AdminLevelCollection, etc. Moreover, entries for 'vendor' and 'composer.lock' are also added to the '.gitignore' of 'alexpechkarev/google-maps' package.

Update ReminderTest to use User model data
This commit modifies the ReminderTest console command to use the User model for fetching user data when sending a reminder mail. Instead of hardcoding 'Vakea' as the user in the reminder mail, it now retrieves the user instance using the provided email and passes it to the ReminderMail class.

Add ReminderTest console command
This commit introduces a new console command called "ReminderTest". This command creates a mock event and sends a reminder email for it based on the information provided inside the handle function. It's meant for testing reminder mail functionality, ensuring that reminders are sent correctly for events.

Update Invoice Command and sections within Invoice and Transactions views
The Invoice Command and Transaction view files were updated to use a getter for order id and show a dynamic contact address. Also, the PurgeDummyData command was enhanced to include deletion of data from the Order Invoice model. In Transaction views, instead of directly accessing the order id property, the getter method has been used. The Invoice Command now uses the email from ShopSettings as the contact address. Furthermore, dummy data from the OrderInvoice model can now be purged using the PurgeDummyData command.
